This paper discusses the role of optimization in deep learning models and their generalization ability, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on the geometry of the parameter space of deep networks, which is a key aspect of optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
